Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - This paper focuses on automatic keyphrase generation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the scope of cs.CL. 
2. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - Keyphrase generation is also relevant to information retrieval, as it can help improve search results and document indexing. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The proposed CorrRNN architecture is a sequence-to-sequence model, which is a common type of neural network used in machine learning. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - Keyphrase generation is a task that can be tackled using various AI techniques, such as NLP and machine learning. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The proposed CorrRNN architecture is a neural network model, which falls under the scope of cs.NE.
